text: @ChrisCullison4 @WPTV I lived on Longboat Key back in the early 70's (before Arvida arrived) after moving there from the U.S.V.I. Back then a red tide was a 2- or 3-week event at the most and didn't occur every year. Now it's a yearly event occurring for months at a time along with blue-green algae..
